        "subject": "LU-19813 build: detect arch with $(uname -m) in O2IBDIR_PATH",
        "message": "LU-19813 build: detect arch with $(uname -m) in O2IBDIR_PATH\n\nOn a ppc64le system, ${target_cpu} outputs powerpc64le\ninstead of ppc64le, which causes an incorrect O2IBDIR_PATH.\nThis patch fixes the above issue by using $(uname -m)\ninstead of ${target_cpu} to detect the system architecture.\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/65051\nLustre-commit: TBD (from bb1d3839dcff8cfd51333ab9ad47a181ef7e6fc0)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial nettype=o2ib\nFixes: aea9738642 (\"LU-18002 build: proper MOFED detection with multiple installations\")\nSigned-off-by: Jian Yu <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5aacd0b1b3dbfa0dc469e58d71972fc64c4b3bd0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_15"
    }
